        <section class="description" id="description">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-history"></i> About Chilkur Balaji Temple</h2>
            <p>Chilkur Balaji Temple, popularly known as the "Visa Balaji Temple," is a revered Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Venkateswara. Located on the outskirts of Hyderabad, this temple attracts thousands of devotees, especially those seeking visas for international travel, earning its unique nickname.</p>

            <div class="historical-fact">
                The temple, believed to be over 500 years old, was constructed during the reign of the Vijayanagara Empire. It is said that devotees who complete 108 circumambulations (pradakshinas) around the temple have their wishes fulfilled.
            </div>

            <p>The temple is known for its unique ritual of offering 108 pradakshinas, where devotees walk around the sanctum sanctorum to seek blessings. The serene environment and spiritual ambiance make it a must-visit for those seeking peace and divine intervention.</p>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 20px; color: var(--hyderabad-blue);"><i class="fas fa-pray"></i> Key Features</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>108 Pradakshina ritual for wish fulfillment</li>
                <li>Simple yet powerful architecture</li>
                <li>No VIP or special darshan queues</li>
                <li>Peaceful surroundings with greenery</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

